answers.answer: Thank you! It's been a rough road but worth it 100%

I am very happy for you , however, pregnancy hypertension is generally not diet related. It's a reaction to the hormones.  I had pregnancy hypertension ONLY with my first pregnancy.Always best to eat a healthy diet but hypertension during pregnancy is not like regular hypertension which is diet related some of the time, but is a precursor to hypertension when someone gets olderGlad you are doing better.  peace

question: So I started having all the signs of preeclampsia at 21 weeks. I changed my diet (after seeing a dietitian), started taking liquid fish oils 2X per day, and Powder magnesium.... I'm now 28 weeks and have no signs of preeclampsia!! God is SOOOOO GOOD!!! Prayer works!!
